verses.text: Praise ye the LORD. Praise, O ye servants of the LORD, praise the name of the LORD.
Blessed be the name of the LORD from this time forth and for evermore.
From the rising of the sun to the going down of the same the LORD'S name isto be praised.
The LORD ishigh above all nations, andhis glory above the heavens.
Who islike to the LORD our God, who dwelleth on high.
Who humbleth himselfto behold the things that arein heaven, and in the earth!
He raiseth the poor out of the dust, andlifteth the needy out of the dunghill;
That he may set himwith princes, evenwith the princes of his people.
He maketh the barren woman to keep house, and to bea joyful mother of children. Praise ye the LORD.
